.TH "fill_write_buffer" 9 "fill_write_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fill_write_buffer \- copy buffer from userspace.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fill_write_buffer
.BI "(struct configfs_buffer * buffer "  ","
.BI "const char __user * buf "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buffer" 12
data buffer for file.
.IP "buf" 12
data from user.
.IP "count" 12
number of bytes in \fIuserbuf\fP.

Allocate \fIbuffer->page\fP if it hasn't been already, then
copy the user-supplied buffer into it.
